-- BUZZ-Mediobanca says no contacts with Bollore to control Telecom Italia
-- 
-- Wed Oct 08, 2014 09:29AM EDT
-- None



Oct 8 (Reuters) -    ** Italian bank Mediobanca <MDBI.MI> CEO Alberto Nagel rules out contacts with Vivendi <VIV.PA> Chairman Vincent Bollore or with other Telecom Italia <TLIT.MI> shareholders aimed at forming pact to control the Italian phone group.

** "I rule it out," Nagel tells reporters on the sidelines of a presentation in Milan. ** Mediobanca reaffirms it wants to sell its 1.6 percent stake in Telecom Italia shortly, he says. The bank has said it would exit Telecom Italia by June 2015. ** Mediobanca used to control Telecom Italia along with Telefonica <TEF.MC>, Intesa Sanpaolo <ISP.MI> and Generali <GASI.MI> via a holding called Telco. Telco is in the process of being dissolved.  ** All members of the Telco vehicle have taken steps to sell their stakes in Telecom Italia, making the company a potential takeover target.(RM:gianluca.semeraro.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net; RM:danilo.masoni.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net)